   [VALENCAY-VISUEL-RENAISSANCE_WEB_HD_CROP.jpg]

The Renaissance
of Valençay

With a Renaissance and classic architecture, ranked among the 22 major sites
of the Loire Valley, the castle of Valençay, excpetional by its location
overlooking the Nahon Valley, offers the charm of the countryside near major
cities. Located between the Berry and the Loire Valley, it is 1 hour from
Tours, 1:30 from Orléans and only 2:30 from Paris.

   [logo-header.png]

   EVENTS
     __________________________________________________________________

Festival Talleyrand

   After its fourth edition, the 2019 Talleyrand Festival will take place
   every weekend from September 7 to 29. This music festival featuring
   ancient instruments, launched in 2014, is becoming a major event, with
   a loyal audience.
   More

   IFRAME: //www.youtube.com/embed/Jwi9BvZxEHg
     __________________________________________________________________

Jazz by Candlelight

   True event of the summer, the candlelight evenings are renewed this
   year around a jazz programming. Laurent Dehors and his Ensemble Tous
   Dehors will take the public on a nocturnal tour of the 3000-candle lit
   castle and park, with an exceptional opera / jazz concert on the large
   lawn.
   More

   IFRAME: //www.youtube.com/embed/xSXEf3Gbslo

     __________________________________________________________________

   INFORMATIONS
     __________________________________________________________________

Opening hours

   Château de Valençay is open everyday from 10:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.
     __________________________________________________________________

Visitor information

   For security reasons, the labyrinth is temporarily closed. We apologize
   in advance for the inconvenience.
     __________________________________________________________________

Gourmet Thursdays

   The next event will be held on Thursday, 3^rd October between 3:30 p.m.
   and 4:30 p.m. in the Office des Cuisines with Alain Lavaud, the chef of
   “Les Saisons Gourmandes” restaurant in St Pierre de Jards.
     __________________________________________________________________

